# Manual HTTP probes for the lending module (Phase 3 / Slice 7).
#
# How to use:
#   1. Start the server with `task run`.
#   2. Open this file in JetBrains GoLand/IntelliJ or in VSCode with the
#      REST Client extension installed.
#   3. Click the gutter icon next to a request to send it.
#
# Substitute <memberId> / <copyId> / <bookId> / <loanId> after the
# corresponding POSTs return.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### POST {{baseUrl}}/loans — borrow an AVAILABLE copy
# Pre-req: POST /members + POST /books + POST /books/{bookId}/copies.
POST {{baseUrl}}/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "memberId": "<memberId>",
  "copyId": "<copyId>"
}

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/loans/<loanId>/return — return a loan
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/loans/<loanId>/return

### POST {{baseUrl}}/reservations — queue a reservation for a book
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "memberId": "<memberId>",
  "bookId": "<bookId>"
}
